						               													<description>Bees are the main theme of this game. You can find honey combs with values from one to ten, but also the queen bee, worth zero. Zero for a queen bee sounds nothing, but that's what the game is about: Gathering as little points as possible, as the games name suggests. Besides the honey combs there are a few action cards, worth twenty points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the begin of the game, each player is dealt hidden cards, he may peek at two of them. Game proceeds in clockwise order, players draw a card. Action cards are executed immediately, honey combs and queen bees may replace any of the hidden cards or be discarded. If a player thinks, that he has the least score in his hidden cards, he can announce the end of the round. Everybody else has one more turn, then the cards are revealed. Each player gets points according to his cards. If the announcer does not have the least score, he is fined additional points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game leaves out any kind of plastic packaging, a percentage of the revenue is donated to projects protecting bees.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
